  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislations\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n\n3. Key Regulatory Elements\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping mandates\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Common Legal Requirements\n- Financial institutions must report suspicious activities\n- Mandatory identification verification\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment protocols\n\n6. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have varying strictness of implementation\n- Compliance requirements differ across regions\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
